  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When things went bad for the German army in Russia, and this started in 1943, and they got the big beating at Stalingrad, and everybody heard about this, and the Germans started to think twice if-- to [PAUSES] act against the Jews or the Romanians who were even milder than them, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS], everybody was thinking of running away from Iasi to avoid the fight, which will probably occur between the Germans from Romanians and the Red Army, which was a great offensive.",
      "word_count": 85
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So then we started preparations for leaving Iasi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The situation in the country was havoc, because thousands and thousands of people of refugees were leaving the eastern part of Romania, which was at the border of Russia, to the south and the west to avoid the coming of the Russian Army.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we were amongst them, with one difference, that we were Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So first priority in the refugees' trains, which were overcrowded with lots of Christian refugees, [CLEARS THROAT] were sometimes [PAUSES] unavailable for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the Jews, they started with their normal tactic, bribing to get some place, secure a miserable little place for-- a compartment for 20, 40 people in a train, a crowded train.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And this is what happened in the spring, March of 1944, when we managed to get a compartment for the whole family in one of the crowded trains through sheer bribery [PAUSES] of Romanian officers, because the trains were under Army control.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where were you going to?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our next destination was Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
